commit.message: Add missing math library as LDFLAG
added missing requests for the repeat interval

fixed: using math functions in util, but failed to link libm.

The new utility functions added to libspnav 1.x use trigonometric and
sqrt functions from the math library, but linking to libm was previously
omitted from the makefile.

Closes bug report #20.
fixed spnav_sensitivity proto1 was sending garbage
fly example: minor comment fix
fix IRIX build
Makefile.in: cleandist -> distclean

change the send_string function, to accept null pointers and send them
as empty strings.
Fix path in configure

fix no-x11 build: some new functions were erroneously declared inside
the USE_X11 conditional block.
preferentially include local spnav_config.h in spnav.h

silence spurious error message from configure when building outside the
git repo
changed the USE_X11 macro to SPNAV_USE_X11
Makefile: make CC and AR assignments ?=
minor formatting fix in readme
updated readme, added documentation links
documentation
much nicer fly example

adding new example to show off how to manipulate the view to fly around
a scene with the new utility functions, and also to show how to
integrate libspnav input into a select loop.
updated the cube example to use the new utility functions

added utility functions for accumulating motion events into posrot
structures, which include a position vector and orientation quaternion,
and then extracting a matrix from that, either for object manipulation
(model matrix), or for view/camera manipulation (view matrix).
new raw axis/button events
forgot to implement spnav_evmask
always flush input before sending a new request to avoid de-syncs
started writing a manual
moved source code under src/
allow sending empty strings
fixed comment about the return value of spnav_dev_name

- fixed makefile, the new proto.o file was missing from the objects list
- make sure all global symbols have spnav_ prefixes to avoid namespace
  pollution.

converted spnav string queries to use the improved version of the
protocol for transmitting strings
